<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Dane" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Dane,</orth> a native of Denmark: <bibl n="shak. aww 4.1.78" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 1, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.281" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 281</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.352" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 352</bibl>. Danes known as great drinkers: <bibl n="shak. ham 1.4.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 4, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 79</bibl><lb />== king of Denmark: <cit><quote>liegemen to the D.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 15</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>you cannot speak of reason to the D. and lose your voice,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.2.44" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 44</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.4.45" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.336" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 336</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>